                            <comment id="13808496" author="jpangburn" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 21:43:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To test these, expand the samples into the corresponding 2.7.6 or 2.7.7 installation&apos;s samples directory.  Run by start the server in one terminal:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mvn -P server&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And after it starts, then the client in another:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mvn -P client&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2.7.6, you&apos;ll see the response from the server printed out on the client indicating success.  In 2.7.7, you&apos;ll see a long output from the schema validation system about why it failed.  If you look for the first &quot;SEVERE&quot; log output, you&apos;ll see it talking about recursion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13809410" author="dkulp" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2013 17:54:15 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;MSV does NOT like two schemas with the same targetNamespace with different systemIds.   This happens when you have a schema that then &quot;includes&quot; a schema of the same namespace.  That&apos;s what your WSDL is doing. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been able to work around some of those issues.  Hopefully this will work going forward. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13809516" author="jpangburn" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2013 19:43:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have tested the 2.7.8-SNAPSHOT against this test case and it works great!  Thanks Dan!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
